post_text:
https://youtu.be/Sw3r2lytys8

This is what I was explaining to you guys today!. Its not about how much you lift (Check your ego's at the door) Its about doing the correct movements. The weight will come once those muscles are conditioned the correct way. I don't tell you guys these things just to hear myself talk, or to get you hurt. If done correctly, you will gain, grow, get stronger and faster. We are trying to prevent injuries by doing things the right way. Make sure you get enough rest at night as well, you grow when you sleep. clean protein before bed so you are feeding those muscles what they need to heal. Great job today, and keep it up.!
